“We now have almost 1 000 employees in the country. The next step is to bring a retail offering to Australia,” the company said. Amazon already sells Kindle e-reader devices, audio books and content through its Australian website. The Sydney Morning Herald reported that Amazon was actively looking for a warehouse, the first of many planned for Australia, with a floor space of up to 93 000m². Read also: Amazon walking away from $1bn deal? According to analysts Roy Morgan, more than 8.7 million Australian consumers bought one or more product on the internet in any given four-week period last year. DPA